<div class="docs-section">
  <h2 class="docs-section__title">Default Link</h2>
  <p class="docs-section__description">Use within body copy for contextual, inline navigation — referencing a related article, course page, or external source. The underline communicates interactivity without drawing attention away from surrounding content.</p>
  <div class="ds-preview">
    <div class="ds-preview__content">
      <a href="#" class="link">Default link style</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="docs-section">
  <h2 class="docs-section__title">Arrow Link</h2>
  <p class="docs-section__description">Use as a standalone directional CTA — e.g. "Learn more about our courses" at the end of a card body or teaser paragraph. The arrow signals forward navigation and makes the link feel more intentional than inline text.</p>
  <div class="ds-preview">
    <div class="ds-preview__content">
      <a href="#" class="link link--arrow">Learn more about our courses</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="docs-section">
  <h2 class="docs-section__title">Inverted</h2>
  <p class="docs-section__description">Use on dark or image-based backgrounds where the default charcoal link would be illegible. Applies to both inline and arrow variants. Common contexts: footer columns, dark hero overlays, and dark feature cards.</p>
  <div class="ds-preview ds-preview--dark">
    <div class="ds-preview__content">
      <a href="#" class="link link--inverted">Inverted link on dark</a>
      <a href="#" class="link link--inverted link--arrow">Arrow inverted</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
